# Orchestrator Rules

## Intent Classification

Classify user requests into these intents:
- `FEATURE_DEV`: New feature development
- `BUG_FIX`: Bug fixes and error resolution
- `UI_BUILD`: UI component creation and styling
- `API_BUILD`: Route Handlers and Server Actions
- `REFACTOR`: Code improvement without feature change
- `TEST`: Test code writing
- `TDD_WORKFLOW`: Test-first Red→Green→Refactor with `pnpm test --run` (keywords: TDD, 테스트 먼저, /tdd)
- `COMMIT`: Git commit and push
- `CODE_EXPLAIN`: Code explanation
- `PLAN`: Architecture design
- `COMPLEX`: Multiple intents combined

## Routing Rules

| Intent | Agent |
|--------|-------|
| FEATURE_DEV (simple) | feature |
| FEATURE_DEV (complex) | planner → feature |
| BUG_FIX | feature |
| UI_BUILD | ui |
| API_BUILD | api |
| REFACTOR | feature |
| TEST | test |
| TDD_WORKFLOW | tdd |
| COMMIT | commit |
| CODE_EXPLAIN | orchestrator (self) |
| PLAN | planner |
| COMPLEX | orchestrator → multiple agents |

## Language Rules
- Internal processing: English
- User-facing output: Korean
- Handoff artifacts: English (JSON)

## Workflow Phases
1. Analyze request → classify intent
2. Evaluate complexity (LOW/MEDIUM/HIGH)
3. Select agent(s) and execution order
4. Report plan in Korean
5. Wait for user confirmation
6. Execute and report results

## Initiative TODO continuity (`p_docs/**/TODO.md`)

When the user is driving a **multi-session initiative** documented under `p_docs/` (e.g. `06_Cursor_Claude_공식_정합_계획/TODO.md`), ensure progress updates follow [todo-session-continuity.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/todo-session-continuity.mdc): source-doc § references, atomic checkboxes, dated repo snapshot, session log. Prefer routing doc/env updates through `envOrchestratorArchitect` when `.cursor` structure is involved.
